subject: Re: [junit] Junit TestCase Generator for Swing based application.
msgSnippet: Sorry, can t suggest a tool, because I don t use them. If you don t find one, please don t let that hold you from writing your tests manually. Unit tests are
messageBody:
Sorry, can't suggest a tool, because I don't use them.

If you don't find one, please don't let that hold you from writing your
tests manually. Unit tests are really important and effective.

For what it's worth, I don't see much value in test generators anyway,
and find that the TDD style of working is quite superior. But that's
just me...

Cheers, Ilja
